Fellow of the British Academy: Karen Spärck Jones FBA (26 August 1935 – 4 April 2007) was a British computer scientist who was responsible for the concept of inverse document frequency, a technology that underlies most modern search engines.

IEEE Emanuel R. Piore Award: She received the IEEE Emanuel R. Piore Award in 2011.

American Academy of Arts and Sciences: In 2007, she was elected a Fellow of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences, and in 2009 was inducted into the National Academy of Engineering.

Peabody Award: She has received awards including the Mystery Writers of America's Edgar Award, the Writers Guild of America Award for Episodic Drama, the Hispanic Images Imagen Award, and the Peabody Award, all for her work on "NYPD Blue".

National Academy of Engineering: Widom is also a member of the National Academy of Engineering.
